The Tokyo Metropolitan Government publishes its open data — including the
日英対訳辞書 (English-Japanese Translation Glossary) — under the Creative
Commons Attribution 4.0 International License. The dataset may be
redistributed, modified, and used commercially provided attribution is
given.

Attribution
-----------

When redistributing the data (including derived works such as glossary
files that incorporate Tokyo entries), credit the source as follows:

  Source: 東京都 日英対訳辞書 (Tokyo Metropolitan Government,
  English-Japanese Translation Glossary). Licensed under CC-BY 4.0.
  https://catalog.data.metro.tokyo.lg.jp/

Notes
-----

This LICENSE accompanies the bundled curated sample CSV in this directory
(`en-ja-translation.csv`, ~30 entries) shipped with translation-toolkit
v0.1.0. It also applies to any full-dataset replacement the operator
manually downloads per `README.md`. The original Tokyo distribution is an
.xlsx file; the parser also accepts .xlsx if `openpyxl` is installed.
